The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a meta learning approach to VQA, which involves learning to learn, and thus could also be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
